ed antenna pattern and how efficiently it\nilluminates the absorber load. We achieved a combined uncertainty as low as 4 K\nfor a 40 K measurement of beam equivalent noise temperature. The measurement\nand analysis techniques described in this paper were pursued to support\nnoise-performance verification of prototype phased-array feeds for the\nAustralian Square Kilometre Array Pathfinder telescope.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 7 Feb 2014 03:42:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-04-04"}
